# sdlc.config — ALL of this instance's bespoke configuration, in one committed
# file at the product-repo root. bootstrap.sh reads it (and writes it for you on
# first run); edit + re-run bootstrap any time — provisioning is idempotent.
#
# NO SECRETS IN THIS FILE — it is committed. Tokens (GH_TOKEN, BOARD_TOKEN_CMD)
# go in each worktree's .env.local (gitignored); AWS credentials stay in
# ~/.aws/credentials and are only *referenced* here by profile name.

INSTANCE="my-product"                 # short slug: seat-file + overlay name
REPO="you/my-product"                 # the product repo on GitHub (owner/repo)
OWNER="you"                           # project-board owner (your login or org)
BASE="$HOME/Code"                     # where the seat checkouts live

# Seats: space-separated role:Name pairs — optionally role:Name:model triples.
# The NAME is the seat's identity — its checkout is $BASE/<repo>-<name>
# (lowercased), its launcher/.app is <Name>.app, and producer seats get a
# seat:<name> routing lane label.
# The MODEL is the seat's Claude tier, written to its .env.local as SEAT_MODEL:
#   omitted → role default (pm + quality-engineer → opus: judgment + the
#   independent gate; everyone else → sonnet: gated, high-volume work).
#   Values: opus · sonnet · haiku, or a pinned model id (claude-…). Aliases
#   float with releases — prefer them; pin only when reproducibility matters.
# Roles: pm · engineer · scrum-master · quality-engineer · cloud-architect ·
#        data-architect · data-scientist   (a role may appear twice — names
#        must be unique; the wizard suggests names, e.g. Pim · Finn · Cas ·
#        Noor · Vera · Otto · Dex · Max · Sam · Tess)
SEATS="pm:Pim engineer:Finn scrum-master:Cas:haiku quality-engineer:Noor engineer:Dex:opus"

# Git identity every seat commits as (applied per-worktree, never globally)
GIT_USER_NAME="Your Name"
GIT_USER_EMAIL="you@example.com"

# AWS — the ~/.aws profile seats use (blank = no AWS). Optionally pin the
# account: bootstrap verifies `sts get-caller-identity` matches when set.
AWS_PROFILE=""
AWS_ACCOUNT_ID=""

# Bootstrap behaviour
SEED_EPIC="y"                         # seed the guided first epic on first run
BUILD_APPS="y"                        # macOS: wrap each seat in a .app bundle
GOLDEN_BOARD=""                       # optional: an existing configured Delivery
                                      # project NUMBER (same owner) to copy via
                                      # copyProjectV2 — its VIEWS + fields travel
                                      # with the copy, so no manual UI step
                                      # remains. Blank = raw create + the one-time
                                      # UI views step (workflow/project-boards.md)
